# Project: e2e_live_chat
# A live two-way WebSocket: an outside caller opens a socket at /chat; the echo
# node holds the conversation, replying to each message with {echo, turn}. The
# rig opens the socket, sends two messages, and asserts the echoes come back.

sock = LiveSocket { path: "__E2E_PATH__" }
echo = LiveWsEcho
out = Debug

echo.started = sock.started
out.data = echo.done
